						               													<description>BEEctionary is a hex tile placement word game. The game allows players to play in 12 various languages - English, German, French, Russian, Turkish, Arabic, Persian, Italian, Spanish, Portuguese, Dutch and Azerbaijani (all letter tiles are included in one box).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal is to create in each round the longest word no one can beat by placing only one letter tile each turn. The game starts with bee hex that could be used as any letter during active player's turn. The word can be in any direction as long as all hex tiles to be used are adjacent and in proper sequence. After each round winner of the round takes all hexes he/she used on his longest word. Next round starts with the next player and with all tiles left on the table after winner of previous round gets his tiles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Player scores 1 point for each letter and 3 points for bee hex. The one who reaches 20 points first is the winner of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
